-- Restaurant and arcade chain Dave & Buster's shares rise in debut
-- By Avik Das in Bangalore and Neha Dimri
-- Fri Oct 10, 2014 10:32AM EDT
-- None



Oct 10 (Reuters) - Shares of Dave & Buster's Entertainment Inc <PLAY.O> rose as much as 13 percent in their market debut on Friday, valuing the restaurant and arcade chain at just over $700 million.

The initial public offering raised about $94 million, after the shares were priced at $16 per each, the low-end of the expected range of $16 to $18. [ID:nGNXVBSYJa] The company, controlled by private equity firm Oak Hill Capital Partners, sold all of the 5.88 million shares offered. The shares opened at $17 on the Nasdaq and touched a high of $18.